Yes, Ren thought. He felt his mana drain to zero.
"I don't have anything," Ren said to Aris.
She looked at him for a long time, then reached into her pocket and pulled out a small, old-fashioned brass key. She set it on the bedside table.
"That's for a locker in the Old Library," she said. "The section they haven't digitized yet. If you want to know why a 'Zero' was admitted to this school in the first place, look for the file marked 'Project Architect'."
She turned to leave, but stopped at the door. "And Ren? Stay away from Kaelen. He’s being fast-tracked for an S-Rank promotion this afternoon. The Association wants to 'upgrade' him immediately to make up for the Site 9 failure."
The door closed. Ren was alone.
He looked at the key, then at the notification flickering in the corner of his eye.
